Subject: Client DPI Enables support for deprecated TLS versions and weak cipher suites
Description:
Hello Support Team,

When DPI is enabled in the endpoint, the MitM enables support for deprecated TLS versions and weak cipher suites, even though when DPI is disabled, the default browser behaviour is safer.

DPI should not decrease the level of security when enabled.
What_We_Know__c: When DPI is enabled, the MitM enables support for deprecated TLS versions and weak cipher suites
Next_Steps__c:
A test build was sent which should address some of the weak cipher suites.
Waiting for the customer to test the build
Solution_Comment__c: The new ticket has the fix for the weak cihers.
